719310f-a.text:
(1)
84-86 Division Street, north side, from Forsyth (left), to Eldridge (right) Streets. Also shown is Eldridge Street, west side, north from Division, to and including Canal Streets. The Elevated on Division Street, is the Second Ave. Line.
June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same; at a later date.
October 11, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.

719753f-a.text:
Forsyth Street, east side, from Division Street to East Broadway.
Note the Second Ave. Elevated on Division Street.
June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
719753f-a.folder: Forsyth Street & Division Street, Manhattan, NY

719757f-b.text:
Forsyth and Eldridge Streets, at their convergence at Division Street. The latter thoroughfare is on the right and is darkened by the "El" line thereupon. A gasoline station appears at the apex formed. Forsyth Street is on the left and Eldridge Street on the right. Overhead, though not shown
is the Manhattan Bridge (Canal Street).
April 6, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr

719756f-a.text:
Forsyth Street, at the N.E. corner of Division Street. Shown across the demolition, are the rears of buildings which front on the west side of Eldridge
Street.
July 23, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
